sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects an executable, which is not an internet browser, making DNS request to legit popular websites, which were seen to be used as dead drop resolvers in previous attacks.
It is extremely abnormal for svchost.exe to spawn without any CLI arguments and is normally observed when a malicious process spawns the process and injects code into the process memory space.
Detects the Setting of Windows Defender Exclusions

match_context.values: @{EventID=1; CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe}

@{EventID=1; CommandLine="%windir%\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="%windir%\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=%windir%\System32\netsh.exe}
